word: Let us, therefore, make every effort
parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Active - 1st Person Plural
str2: To hasten, be eager, be zealous. From spoude; to use speed, i.e. To make effort, be prompt or earnest.
To go in, come in, enter. From eis and erchomai; to enter.
That, that one there, yonder. From ekei; that one (neuter) thing); often intensified by the article prefixed.
From katapauo; reposing down, i.e. abode.
In order that, so that. Probably from the same as the former part of heautou; in order that.
Not, lest. A primary particle of qualified negation; not, lest; also (whereas ou expects an affirmative one) whether.

parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: Any one, some one, a certain one or thing. An enclitic indefinite pronoun; some or any person or object.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: A reduplicated and contracted form of peto; probably akin to petomai through the idea of alighting; to fall.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Dative Neuter 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
(a) a figure, copy, (b) an example, model. From hupodeiknumi; an exhibit for imitation or warning.
Willful unbelief, obstinacy, disobedience. From apeithes; disbelief.
